<title type="html"><![CDATA[Cartidge edge /IRQ]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5363&amp;p=48513#p48513"><![CDATA[
I'd bet the same thing as on the NES: to let the cartridge generate an interrupt. It's less needed for raster effects than on the NES because of the built-in scanline counter and HDMA, but it's still there when needed. I seem to remember that the SA-1 can interrupt the main CPU and vice versa.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Jul 02, 2009 7:18 pm</p><hr />
